<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-queFraccionTieneSentido" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><ol>
<li>Any numerator greater than 2. Sample response: These numerators all show more than 2 eighths.</li>
<li>
<m>\frac{1}{2}</m>, <m>\frac{2}{4}</m>, or <m>\frac{4}{8}</m>. Sample response: These fractions are all equivalent to <m>\frac{3}{6}</m>.</li>
<li>4, 6, or 8. Sample response: These denominators have smaller parts than thirds, so 4 parts of these sizes will be smaller than 4 thirds.</li>
</ol>
      </li>
      <li><p>Sample responses:</p> 
        <ol>
<li>Less: <m>\frac{2}{6}</m>,  <m>\frac{2}{6} &lt; \frac{4}{6}</m> More: <m>\frac{7}{6}</m>, <m>\frac{7}{6} &gt; \frac{4}{6}</m> Equivalent: <m>\frac{2}{3}</m>, <m>\frac{2}{3} = \frac{4}{6}</m>
</li>
<li>Less: <m>\frac{1}{4}</m>, <m>\frac{1}{4} &lt; \frac{3}{4}</m> More: <m>\frac{5}{4}</m>,  <m>\frac{5}{4} &gt; \frac{3}{4}</m> Equivalent: <m>\frac{6}{8}</m>, <m>\frac{6}{8} = \frac{3}{4}</m>
</li>
</ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


